Full Stack Developer (PHP/Vue)
#удаленка #senior #400k
Company: HypeAuditor
Salary: до 4 500$
Формат работы: удаленный в любой стране мире (есть юрлица в Сербии и на Кипре, в этих странах возможно трудоустройство в штат и помощь с легализацией)
We are developing a HighLoad product focused on the international market, working with a lot of data, ML, AI and other interesting technologies. For 5 years we have been creating services and features that have no analogues, and we are leaders in terms of the quality analytics among the participants. And now our friendly team needs reinforcements.
Briefly about us: we are making a B2B product that helps a variety of companies successfully promote their products and brands with influencers. We cover well-known social media networks - Instagram, YouTube, Snapchat, TikTok, Twitter, and Twitch - and are working on expanding this list.‍
Our stack:
— PHP 7/8;
— Vue / Nuxt;
— JS (ES6);
— HTML5 и CSS3;
— MySQL / MongoDB;
— Redis, RabbitMQ.‍
Requirements:
— experience with Vue, JavaScript (ES6);
— experience with PHP 7/8, ability to write clean maintainable code;
— proficiency in current HTML5 and CSS3 standards, staying updated on new trends in client-side development (frameworks; CSS post- and preprocessors);
— experience with Sass/SCSS;
— proficiency in version control systems (Git);
— experience with MongoDB and understanding of its operation;
— understanding of SOLID / DRY principles.
Corporate benefits:
— the opportunity to work under a labor contract from anywhere in the world or the possibility of employment in countries where we have legal entities (Cyprus/Serbia). We assist with legalization in these countries;
— 100% paid sick leave, 20 working days of annual leave per year, the option to choose days off for public holidays (an additional 13 days of annual leave per year);
— equipment for work;
— medical insurance in your country after the probation period;
— many opportunities for learning and improving skills, internal trainings, workshops, and also language clubs (English, French, German, Serbian, Spanish).
Send your resume and ask a question about the vacancy
